Subject: Navier-Stokes Pressure Tail Target Prospect

Description: Bounded target-prospecting pass for the Navier-Stokes bridge obstruction after the quiet-watch idleness correction.

& [NavierStokesPressureTailTargetProspect] is a target_prospecting record
  + [project] is seven math problems
  + [created_at] is 2026-06-27
  + [reentry_commit] is 7f5e8b4 Correct quiet watch research idleness
  + [lane] is Navier-Stokes
  + [missing_bridge] is no_tail_budget_to_pressure_oscillation_or_L3_over_2_smallness_lemma
  + [authority_boundary] is proof_blocked
  + [not_claimed] is no regularity proof, no lock-mass reduction, and no validation of the project-local pressure-tail route

& [ProspectQuery] is the bounded search question
  + [query] is identify accepted theorem interfaces connecting pressure control, local energy inequality, scale-critical smallness, and Escauriaza-Seregin-Sverak type criteria
  + [purpose] is find a concrete theorem target for later audit
  + [not_purpose] is deriving the missing bridge during this pass

& [CandidateInterfaceSet] is the target neighborhood found
  + [candidate_001_caffarelli_kohn_nirenberg] is partial regularity and epsilon-regularity framework for suitable weak solutions
    = source: Caffarelli, Kohn, and Nirenberg, Partial regularity of suitable weak solutions of the Navier-Stokes equations, Communications in Pure and Applied Mathematics 35(6), 771-831, 1982, doi 10.1002/cpa.3160350604
    = url: https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/cpa.3160350604
    = relevance: gives the local energy and scale-critical pressure/velocity environment into which a pressure-tail estimate would need to fit
    = limitation: does not by itself convert a tail budget into the required smallness quantity
  + [candidate_002_escauriaza_seregin_sverak] is endpoint L-infinity-time L3-space regularity via backward uniqueness
    = source: Escauriaza, Seregin, and Sverak, L3,infinity-solutions of the Navier-Stokes equations and backward uniqueness, Russian Mathematical Surveys 58(2), 211-250, 2003
    = url: https://www.pdmi.ras.ru/~seregin/Recent%20Publications/engESS3.pdf
    = relevance: supplies the accepted endpoint-critical target family adjacent to the project's L3 or L3/2 criterion language
    = limitation: the project still lacks a bridge from localized pressure-tail accounting to the global/local critical norm hypothesis
  + [candidate_003_pressure_criteria] is pressure-based regularity criterion literature
    = source: Tran and Yu, Regularity of Navier-Stokes flows with bounds for the pressure, Applicable Analysis 2016 preprint copy
    = url: https://research-repository.st-andrews.ac.uk/bitstream/handle/10023/12230/Tran_2016_Regularity_AML_AAM.pdf?isAllowed=y&sequence=1
    = relevance: directly studies regularity from pressure bounds and is closer to the project's pressure-tail vocabulary than pure velocity criteria
    = limitation: must be audited for whether its pressure bounds match the project's tail object or require a different domain/measure condition
  + [candidate_004_one_scale_epsilon_regularities] is modern one-scale epsilon regularity target
    = source: Albritton, Barker, and Prange, Epsilon regularity for the Navier-Stokes equations via weak-strong uniqueness
    = url: https://prange.perso.math.cnrs.fr/papers/epreg-viaWSU.pdf
    = relevance: offers a compact theorem-interface form for asking whether a project-local estimate can feed an epsilon regularity criterion
    = limitation: still requires exact matching of quantities and hypotheses before it can become a proof-lane target

& [ProspectReading] is the current shape of meaning
  + [found_target] is yes
  + [target_shape] is not a single theorem yet but a target neighborhood around local epsilon regularity plus pressure-control criteria
  + [most_promising_next_audit] is compare the project-local pressure-tail module against pressure criterion hypotheses before attempting ESS endpoint language
  + [reason] is pressure criteria are closest in vocabulary to the missing bridge, while ESS is more authoritative but farther from the project-local tail object
  + [risk] is target drift from pressure-tail accounting into generic regularity-criterion summaries

& [NextBoundedMotion] is the follow-up
  + [mode] is target_prospecting_or_proof_lane_precheck
  + [next_question] is can the project-local tail budget be expressed as a scale-invariant pressure quantity used in a cited pressure regularity criterion
  + [required_artifact] is a hypothesis-matching table with rows for project-tail quantity, accepted theorem quantity, scaling, locality, and missing conversion lemma
  + [Deep_Research_Priority_Gate] is not triggered yet
    = reason: the target neighborhood has enough resolution for one local hypothesis-matching audit
